        <property propertyId="38f94dd1-d5aa-41b8-b182-c0c42985d9dc" amount="0.218397" unitId="7b75baf0-cbee-45e6-bf66-af119da06553">
          <name xml:lang="en">price</name>
          <unitName xml:lang="en">EUR2005</unitName>
          <comment xml:lang="en">The price was calculated based on data on gross value (AUD) [1] divided by the production quantity [2] of maize grain for the years 2017-2020 for the New South Wales region in Australia from the Australian Bureau of Statistics (ABS). Data was available per financial year, so that the first year of the financial year was assumed to be the year analysed. References: [1] Value of Agricultural Commodities Produced, Australia; accessed on 24.08.23, available at: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/industry/agriculture/value-agricultural-commodities-produced-australia [2] Agricultural Commodities, Australia; accessed on 24.08.2023, available at: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/industry/agriculture/agricultural-commodities-australia
The prices were converted to EUR based on the annual exchange rates published by the European Central Bank (https://sdw.ecb.europa.eu/quickview.do?SERIES_KEY=120.EXR.A.AUD.EUR.SP00.A, last accessed on 2023-06-01) and adjusted for inflation relative to 2005 using the producer price index (PPI) of the euro area, published by eurostat (https://ec.europa.eu/eurostat/databrowser/view/STS_INPP_A__custom_6416181/default/table?lang=en, last accessed on 2023-06-01).</comment>
        </property>
